  "text": "The inferior olive provides one of the two main inputs to the olivocerebellum system through the so-called climbing fibers, the other being the mossy fibers. The inferior-olive neurons are also heavily interconnected to one another through direct electrical connections called gap junctions (GJs). The gap junctions define the synchronization behavior between the Inferior-Olive cells and, subsequently, influence the synchronization and learning properties of the overall system [CITATION_1] .",
